"adj. 不付款的，免费的 【英】 adj. 不付款的,免费的(fre e; without charge) 【例】 The service was gratis to clubmembers(该项服 务对俱乐部成员免费) adj. 不付款的, 免费的 【记】g割, rat老鼠, is是: 割老鼠是免费的, 难道人家帮你割老鼠, 你还要收钱? 【记】grateful感激 + is→感激就是对免费服务的感激 gratis  mid-15c., ""for nothing, freely,"" from Latin gratis, contraction of gratiis ""for thanks,"" hence, ""without recompense,"" ablative of gratiae ""thanks,"" plural of gratia ""favor"" (see grace). Meaning ""free of charge"" is 1540s."
